Template: automation-interface-sso/choose_backend
Type: multiselect
Choices: Active Directory, RADIUS
Description: Choose the authentication backend for your setup
  Choose authentication backend

Template: automation-interface-sso/automation_interface_admin_password
Type: password
Description: Insert the password for admin@automation.local (local admin user, who is always enabled to login, even if external identity provider isn't working).
  Admin password

Template: automation-interface-sso/radius_server
Type: string
Description: Insert the FQDN or IP address of the RADIUS server
  RADIUS address

Template: automation-interface-sso/radius_port
Type: string
Description: Insert the port number of the RADIUS server
  RADIUS port

Template: automation-interface-sso/radius_password
Type: password
Description: Insert the password of the RADIUS server
  RADIUS password

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_server
Type: string
Description: Insert the FQDN or IP address of the Active Directory server
  AD address

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_domain
Type: string
Description: Insert the fqdn of the Active Directory domain
  AD Domain

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_token_user
Type: string
Description: Insert the user to connect to the AD server and check the authentication
  AD token user

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_token_passwd
Type: password
Description: Insert the password for user to connect to the AD server and check the authentication
  AD token user password

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_required_group
Type: string
Description: Insert the AD group required to login in the automation tool web interface
  AD Required group

Template: automation-interface-sso/ad_userPrincipalName
Type: boolean
Description: Allow to login using the userPrincipalName as username (eg: user@example.com)
  AD userPrincipalName

Template: automation-interface-sso/ou_users
Type: string
Description: CN/OU where users are found in the active directory (default in AD: CN=Users)
  AD OU users

Template: automation-interface-sso/ou_groups
Type: string
Description: CN/OU where groups are found in the active directory (default in AD: CN=Users)
  AD OU groups

Template: automation-interface-sso/superadmin_AD_groups
Type: string
Description: DN of the active directory groups that are configured as superadmin
